  <summary>3/20/2001--Introduced.
Expresses the sense of Congress that employers of members of the military reserve components should: (1) be commended for their commitment to such employees; and (2) continue to support the mission of such components by strictly adhering to Federal provisions which prohibit adverse employment actions against such employees which are motivated by such reserve involvement.</summary>
